<DIV1 TYPE="eulogy">
<P><PB REF="002180_0026_10030BF314732738">SINCE the Compo&s;ing the Di&s;cour&s;e above, having heard the Melancholly News from Home, of the DEATH of Sir WILLIAM ASHHURST, a Lover of, and Benefactor to our Country; Yea, to the <HI>Briti&s;h</HI> Kingdom, where he had his Re&s;idence: I take this Occa&s;ion, on behalf I of this Obliged People, to expre&s;s our &s;ad Re&s;entment of, and Lamentations for &s;o great a Publick Lo&s;s: And earne&s;t de&s;ires of a continued Succe&s;&s;ion of his NAME, in his Family of Worthy Patriots; who&s;e fragrant Names shall be famous in our <HI>I&s;rael,</HI> for their Worthy Deeds, as His has been, till Time &s;hall be no more.</P>
